==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Agist
<hw>A*gist"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>agister</ets>; <ets>⟦agrave⟧</ets> (L. <ets>ad</ets>) +
<ets>gister</ets> to assign a lodging, fr. <ets>giste</ets> lodging,
abode, F. <ets>g⟦icir⟧te</ets>, LL. <ets>gistum</ets>, <ets>gista</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>jacitum</ets>, p. p. of <ets>jac⟦emac⟧re</ets> to lie: cf.
LL. <ets>agistare</ets>, <ets>adgistare</ets>. See <er>Gist</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>To take to graze or pasture, at a certain sum; --
used originally of the feeding of cattle in the king's forests, and
collecting the money for the same.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Agistator</ent>⟦br⟧
